# Malware Basics

This section covers common types of malware and their functions.
## Backdoor
A backdoor is a type of malware used to gain unauthorized access to a system by bypassing normal authentication procedures.

## Ransomware
Ransomware is malicious software that encrypts or locks a computer system or data and holds it captive until a payment (ransom) is made.

## Scareware
Scareware is a type of malware that uses fear tactics to trick users into taking a specific action, such as installing fake software or paying money.

## Rootkit
A rootkit is designed to modify the operating system to create a hidden backdoor, which attackers can use to access a computer remotely.

## Virus
A virus is a type of malicious computer program that, when executed, replicates itself and attaches to other executable files by inserting its own code.
